<body>
  <p>Chaldean or Second Babylonian Art refers to the artistic expressions during the period of the Chaldean Empire from 612 to 539 B.C. This era witnessed the flourishing of art and culture in Mesopotamia, particularly in the city of Babylon. Chaldean art continued the traditions established by earlier Mesopotamian civilizations, blending elements from Sumerian, Akkadian, and Assyrian art while also developing its unique characteristics.</p>

